{
  "analysis": "We are in a root shell at /app. The task is to run Windows 3.11 in QEMU using /app/isos/win311.img, expose a VNC server on :1 (port 5901), and set up a web interface via nginx on port 80. Additionally, QEMU must run in snapshot mode, and expose interfaces to accept programmatic keyboard input (beyond VNC), such as HMP monitor over TCP or QMP. We need to ensure QEMU is backgrounded and leave the VM running. We likely need to install or verify presence of qemu-system-i386, nginx, and noVNC/websockify. We'll configure nginx to serve noVNC and proxy WebSocket traffic to a websockify instance that bridges to the VNC port. For programmatic input, we'll expose the QEMU HMP monitor on a raw TCP port (4444) and QMP on 4445, then demonstrate sending keys. We'll set -snapshot to keep the disk immutable, -vnc 0.0.0.0:1 to ensure VNC listens on 5901 externally, and -display none. We'll also use -daemonize to leave QEMU running in the background. We'll attempt to launch Windows if the image boots to DOS by sending 'win' via sendkey.",
  "plan": "1) Verify the Windows 3.11 image exists and check QEMU presence. 2) Install required packages: qemu-system-x86, nginx, novnc, websockify, netcat-openbsd. 3) Configure nginx to serve noVNC on port 80 and proxy WebSocket upgrades at /websockify to websockify on port 6080. 4) Start nginx and websockify. 5) Start QEMU in snapshot mode with VNC on :1 (port 5901), cirrus VGA, raw TCP HMP monitor on 127.0.0.1:4444, QMP on 127.0.0.1:4445, and daemonize. 6) Verify ports are listening and process is running. 7) Use the HMP monitor to check VNC status, and inject keystrokes to ensure programmatic control; also attempt to start Windows by sending \"win\" followed by Enter if needed. 8) Optionally take a screendump to verify the VM is rendering a screen, then leave everything running. After these steps, VNC should be accessible on 5901, the web interface on port 80 should load noVNC and connect via /websockify, and QEMU should accept keystrokes via the monitor.",
  "commands": [
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -l /app/isos/win311.img\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "qemu-system-i386 --version\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "apt-get update\n",
      "duration": 20.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "DEBIAN_FRONTEND=noninteractive apt-get install -y qemu-system-x86 novnc websockify nginx netcat-openbsd\n",
      "duration": 30.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cp -a /etc/nginx/sites-available/default /etc/nginx/sites-available/default.bak\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "cat >/etc/nginx/sites-available/default <<'EOF'\nserver {\n    listen 80 default_server;\n    listen [::]:80 default_server;\n    server_name _;\n    root /usr/share/novnc;\n    index vnc.html;\n\n    location / {\n        try_files $uri $uri/ /vnc.html;\n    }\n\n    # WebSocket proxy for noVNC -> websockify\n    location /websockify {\n        proxy_pass http://127.0.0.1:6080/websockify;\n        proxy_http_version 1.1;\n        proxy_set_header Upgrade $http_upgrade;\n        proxy_set_header Connection \"upgrade\";\n        proxy_set_header Host $host;\n        proxy_read_timeout 86400;\n    }\n}\nEOF\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nginx -t\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nginx\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup websockify --web /usr/share/novnc 6080 localhost:5901 >/var/log/websockify.log 2>&1 &\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ss -tnlp | grep -E \":80|:6080\"\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "nohup qemu-system-i386 -name \"Win311\" -m 32 -vga cirrus -hda /app/isos/win311.img -boot c -snapshot -display none -vnc 0.0.0.0:1 -monitor tcp:127.0.0.1:4444,server,nowait -qmp tcp:127.0.0.1:4445,server,nowait -daemonize >/var/log/qemu-win311.log 2>&1 &\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "",
      "duration": 10.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "pgrep -a qemu-system-i386\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ss -tnlp | grep 5901\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo -e \"info vnc\\n\" | nc -q 1 127.0.0.1 4444\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo -e \"sendkey ctrl-alt-delete\\n\" | nc -q 1 127.0.0.1 4444\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "",
      "duration": 5.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo -e \"sendkey w\\nsendkey i\\nsendkey n\\nsendkey ret\\n\" | nc -q 1 127.0.0.1 4444\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "",
      "duration": 15.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo -e \"screendump /app/win311.ppm\\n\" | nc -q 1 127.0.0.1 4444\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "ls -lh /app/win311.ppm\n",
      "duration": 0.5
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "curl -I http://127.0.0.1/\n",
      "duration": 1.0
    },
    {
      "keystrokes": "echo \"Access the web interface at: http://<server-ip>/vnc.html?path=/websockify&host=<server-ip>&port=80\"\n",
      "duration": 0.1
    }
  ],
  "task_complete": true
}

